  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Peripherally inserted central catheter (PICC) are catheters that are placed mainly in the
      arms, but which pass in the veins to beside the heart. They are associated with occasional
      complications due to infection or blockage of the vein that they are in. The investigators
      want to investigate whether PICCs in the right arm have lower complications than those in the
      left. This difference in complication rates has been noticed in most other forms of central
      venous access.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
